When there are many issues on the board, the load time is pretty bad.

We could 'paginate' the results to improve the experience for example. Ie. Once a user scrolls down, we can load the other issues which are ranked below the bottom of the screen.

Edit: incorporating performance for epics and versions

Current state of Sprint after it is completed, you cannot alter the naming of it. Based on the use case provided by customer:

{quote}
Basically it amounts to the fact that when you start a new project naming conventions are not really something you have fully stabilized. When at a later point in the project you want to refit some of your older works to the now more stable conventions it would be nice to be allowed to do this.

In this specific case sprint naming should follow a convention which will allow us to use the api more fluently without taking in to account to many obscure ways of naming sprints.
{quote}

This feature will be good to have in the target of re-organizing things and to be identified more fluently by the api.

